    - rid: 5311918863438577763
      type: {class: FillInTheBlanksItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        question:
        - 'An object must (1)__________ for work to be considered done, and the (2)__________
          must act along the motion of the object.

          The expression to calculate
          work along the x-axis is (3)__________, with W as work, F as force, and
          x as (4)__________.'
        correctAnswers:
        - moves
        - force
        - W = F x
        - displacement
        wrongAnswers:
        - velocity
        - speed
        difficulty: 0
    - rid: 5311918863438577766
      type: {class: FillInTheBlanksItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        question:
        - "The resultant velocity is solved using the equation (1)__________. The
          resultant distance is solved using the equation (2)__________. \r\n\r\nTo
          solve for the angle of displacement, we use the trigonometric ratios known
          as (3)__________. When Vx = 20 m/s and Vy = 15 m/s, the angle of displacement
          is equal to (4)__________.  "
        correctAnswers:
        - "VR = \u221AVx\xB2 + Vy\xB2"
        - "R = \u221Aa\xB2 + b\xB2"
        - "SOH\u2013CAH\u2013TO"
        - "53.13\xB0"
        wrongAnswers:
        - velocity
        - speed
        difficulty: 0
